Latest news
News announcement20 December 2024
Customs: Georgia to join the Common Transit Convention and the Convention on the Simplification of Formalities in Trade in Goods
As of 1 February 2025, Georgia will become the latest country to join the Common Transit Convention and the Convention on the Simplification of Formalities in Trade in Goods.
News announcement20 December 2024
New Computerised Transit System (NCTS): The deployment of the phase 5 is on track
29 countries (Member States and other countries which are part of the Common Transit Convention) have deployed the new phase 5 of NCTS and in all countries the operations are running smoothly.
News announcement19 December 2024
PEM Convention: the Joint Committee decisions paves the Way for Simplified Rules of Origin
On 12 December, the 16th meeting of the Pan-Euro-Mediterranean (PEM) Convention Joint Committee took place in Brussels, marking a significant milestone in the lead-up to the entry into force of the Revised PEM Convention on 1 January 2025.
News announcement18 December 2024
Member States made significant progress in VAT Compliance in 2022, but continued efforts are still needed
Most EU Member States made significant progress in Value-Added Tax (VAT) collection between 2018 and 2022, according to a new report released by the European Commission today.
News announcement17 December 2024
TAX Administration EU summit (TADEUS) took place in Budapest
Heads of Tax Administrations discussed how to address common challenges
